   <mods:abstract>Acknowledges receipt of Duane's letter of 16 May, in reply to John Jay's
            of the 13th,with regrets that Duane made such a painful effort in answering from his
            sickbed. John Jay sent Adams a copy of a letter from Duane on 27 March, but received no
            reply until 19 May. The journals ascribed to John Jay and Adams must be either the
            letters, copies, extracts, or abridgments of those written during the negotiations for
            peace in 1783. John Jay is inclined to think that they are abridgments. He. would like
            to have copies of the journals in order to correct any errors and to see how judiciously
            the abridgments were made. John Jay will forward the copy of Adams' journal on to
            him.</mods:abstract>
